The Anaheim Police Department is the police department of the city of Anaheim, California. The department was created in 1870 when David Davies was elected as the city's first marshal. The department currently employs over 380 sworn officers and upwards of 170 civilian support staff. Anaheim police headquarters are located at 425 S. Harbor Blvd., and there are substations located in each of the East, South, and West divisions.